=========
TC driver
=========
The TC consists of a counter, a prescaler, compare/capture channels and control logic. 
The counter can be set to count events, or it can be configured to count clock pulses. 
It can also perform waveform generation, such as frequency generation and pulse-width 
modulation (PWM).

The timer/counter is clocked by the peripheral clock with optional prescaling.

Features
--------
* Initialization
* Interrupt Callback handling

Applications
------------
* Frequency Generation
* Single-slope PWM (pulse width modulation)
* Dual-slope PWM
* Count on event
* Quadrature decoding

Dependencies
------------
* CLK for clock
* CPUINT/PMIC for Interrupt
* UPDI/PDI/JTAG for debug
* PORT for Waveform Generation

Driver Configuration
--------------------
* **TC Channel configuration in Capture Mode**
   This Scenario shows, how to configure TC channel in Capture Mode. 
   Follow below steps to configure TC0 Instance Channel 0 in Capture Mode.

   #. Select *TCx Channel n mode*. Here x is the TC instance number and n is the 
      TCx Channel number. In below image x is 0(TC0) and n is 0(channel 0). TC0 Channel 0 
      configured in **Capture Mode**.
   #. Click on **CHANNEL0 CONFIGURATION** Enable check box.
   #. Click on **TC_CMR0(CAPTURE MODE) CONFIGURATION** Enable check box.
   #. Do the TC0 Channel 0 Capture mode configiration in green box shown 
      in below image.

   .. raw:: html

      <a href="https://www.microchip.com/" target="_blank">
      <img alt="Scenario-1-TC-Channel-Capture-Mode-Configuration.png" src="data:image/png;base64," /></a>

* **TC Channel configuration in Waveform Mode**
   This Scenario shows, how to configure TC channel in Waveform Mode. 
   Follow below steps to configure TC0 Instance Channel 1 in Waveform Mode.

   #. Select *TCx Channel n mode*. Here x is the TC instance number and n is the 
      TCx Channel number. In below image x is 0(TC0) and n is 1(channel 1). TC0 Channel 1 
      configured in **Waveform Mode**.
   #. Click on **CHANNEL1 CONFIGURATION** Enable check box.
   #. Click on **TC_CMR1(WAVEFORM MODE) CONFIGURATION** Enable check box.
   #. Do the TC0 Channel 1 Waveform mode configiration in green box shown 
      in below image.
